Case called @ 1:03 p.m. Defendant Damian Isiah Moltzau in court with attorney Michael J. Short.  Defendant Damian Isiah Moltzau in custody, appears via video. Attorney Short appears telephonically.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant failed to appear on December 6, 2016. ADA Anderson - Motion to Vacate PPDA has been filed. NC plea had been entered in August of 2015 and the defendant had entered into a PPDA - DE has not complied with the terms of the PPDA. Parties are prepared to proceed to sentencing today.  Defendant waives his right to be personally present in the courtroom. DE agrees that a violation of the terms of the PPDA has occurred. The Court finds that a violation has occurred and enters an order vacating the PPDA. The Court enters JOC. Statement by DE regarding sentencing. Atty Short requesting expungment. ADA Anderson does voice and objection to expungment.  Court orders: 12 days WCJ - 9 days CFTS - Time served sentence, Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA sample and surcharge. The Court declines the opportunity for expungment based on the violation of the terms of the PPDA. Appeal rights given.
